body:
While elaborating the two modules below, Yosys (as of 5c09f24e48db032d36448125508aa3c28c5b2ef4) throws an assertion from `frontends/ast/simplify.cc:3178` for the first module (with one reg) and from `frontends/ast/simplify.cc:3199` for the second module (with two regs). If either the foor-loop or the multi-dimensioanl regs are removed, no assertions are thrown.
``` Verilog
module yosys_constant_function_2(output [7:0] data_o);

   parameter  WIDTH = 3;
   localparam DEPTH = 1 << WIDTH;
   
   function [7:0] lookup(input [WIDTH-1:0] index);
      integer   i;
      reg [7:0] val_table [DEPTH-1:0];
      begin
         for(i = 0; i < DEPTH; i = i + 1) begin
            val_table[i] = ~(i & 32'hFF);
         end
         lookup = val_table[index];
      end
   endfunction

   assign data_o = lookup(2);
   
endmodule
```
``` Verilog
module yosys_constant_function_3(output [7:0] data_o);

   parameter  WIDTH = 3;
   localparam DEPTH = 1 << WIDTH;

   function [7:0] lookup(input select,
                         input [WIDTH-1:0] index);
      integer   i;
      reg [7:0] val_table_a [DEPTH-1:0];
      reg [7:0] val_table_b [DEPTH-1:0];
      begin
         for(i = 0; i < DEPTH; i = i + 1) begin
            val_table_a[i] = ~(i & 8'hFF);
	    val_table_b[i] = ~(i & 8'hF0);
         end
         lookup = (select) ? val_table_a[index] : val_table_b[index];
      end
   endfunction

   assign data_o = lookup(1'b1, 5);
   
endmodule
```
